data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0b5e0165206a21090069deb4f6bfdc819094dfebc0a17ef674","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":241,"text":"\n## [Paris, France](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Paris%2C+France?utm_source=openai)\n\n\nParis is the capital and largest city of France, located in the north-central part of the country along the Seine River. It serves as the nation's political, economic, and cultural center. ([britannica.com](https://www.britannica.com/place/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe name \"Paris\" is derived from the Parisii, a Celtic tribe that inhabited the area from the 3rd century B.C. ([countryreports.org](https://www.countryreports.org/country/france/capital-city.htm?utm_source=openai))\n\nKnown as the \"City of Light,\" Paris has been a major center of finance, diplomacy, commerce, culture, fashion, and gastronomy since the 17th century. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe city is home to iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre Museum, and Notre-Dame Cathedral, attracting millions of tourists annually. ([britannica.com](https://www.britannica.com/facts/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nAs of 2026, Paris has an estimated population of 2.04 million within the city and approximately 13.2 million in its metropolitan area. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe city's administrative body is the Council of Paris, which governs the capital. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nFor a visual overview of Paris, you might find this video informative:\n\n[PARIS | City of Love & Capital of France](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U62W--tn7gs&utm_source=openai)\n "}

